I"[	<h1 id="aris-tutorial---plugins">Aris Tutorial - Plugins</h1>

<p>In this tutorial, we’re going to show you Aris plugins, some of which are cool, others are pretty useful.</p>

<p><strong>clear</strong> enables you to clear all messages in home screen.</p>

<p><strong>restart</strong> apparently will reboot Aris. If things start getting weird, it’s recommended to use this command to reboot Aris.</p>

<p><strong>apps</strong> takes you to a regular app list where you can find all apps, in an old fasion way. This works when you sometimes really can’t find your app.</p>

<p><strong>config</strong> takes you to configuration page.</p>

<p><strong>store</strong> takes you to Aris store.</p>

<p><strong>torch</strong> toggles the flash.</p>

<p><strong>bluetooth</strong> toggles the bluetooth.</p>

<p><strong>wifi</strong> displays the wifi settings as a floating window, like this:</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/plugins-1.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Apart from that, we have a bunch of cool plugins, just to look cool. By using the command, a floating window will show up correspondingly.</p>

<p><strong>locateme</strong> displays a window shows your current location.</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/plugins-2.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p><strong>encrypt</strong> displays a window of encrypting message. BTW, in ‘instant run’ section, you’ll further</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/plugins-3.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-1.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>In order to enable notification display you need to both enable it in Aris and in Android systme. Firstly, go ‘config’ and enable notification.</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-2.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>After you enable notification in Aris configuration, you’ll be directed to system notification settings. Now enable it for the Launcher you are using.</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-3.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Now, go back to home screen and if you see this notification, it means notifiaction has been successfully enabled:</p>

<p> 
<img src="/assets/notification-4.png" alt="" /></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Apart from that, you can also change the styles of the notification in ‘config’. We have 3 notification styles available.</p>

<p> 
Cheers!</p>

